column8: Additional scrubbing required to remove tenacious growth.
Replaced hull anode, starboard side: Diver’s Dream Mini
Will replace strut anode (3-4” trimtab style) on next service, and possibly shaft anode as well.
Replaced strut anode with 3” trim tab style

Electrolysis beginning on prop. I suspect the anode on the prop shaft has become ineffective for some reason. Installed an additional new 1-1/8” heavy duty streamlined on prop shaft. Let’s see if that improves things.
Very light electrolysis appears to be continuing on the prop. None of my prop anodes fit this prop nut, but I will search around to see if one exists that will.
No new electrolysis on prop. Shaft anode appears to be working. Will replace on next service.
Installed streamlined heavy duty 1-1/8” shaft anode
Installed R2 on strut, 1-1/8” heavy duty on shaft
